
Testbed
=======


(1)
Install dependencies:

# get GeoTools 9.0 (no other versions tested), <http://www.geotools.org/>
cd project/lib
# <http://sourceforge.net/projects/geotools/files/GeoTools%209%20Releases/>
# geotools-9.0-bin.zip

# unpack into lib
unzip geotools-9.0-bin.zip

# search for all gt-epsg-*.jar
find . -name gt-epsg\*jar

# delete all of those but one (for example, keep gt-epsg-hsql-9.0.jar)
rm ./geotools-8.5/gt-epsg-oracle-9.0.jar
rm ./geotools-8.5/gt-epsg-wkt-9.0.jar
rm ./geotools-8.5/gt-epsg-extension-9.0.jar
rm ./geotools-8.5/gt-epsg-postgresql-9.0.jar

# (You may also need to remove imageio-ext-imagereadmt-1.1.6.jar from the classpath to prevent runtime error messages. In spite of any errors, execution of this code should not be affected.)

# get TestNG 6.8 (no other version tested)

cd project/lib
curl -O "http://testng.org/testng-6.8.zip"
unzip testng-6.8.zip
mv testng-6.8/testng-6.8.jar .
rm -R testng-6.8.zip testng-6.8

# get args4j 2.0.21 (no other versions tested), <http://args4j.kohsuke.org/>

cd project/lib
curl -O http://maven.jenkins-ci.org/content/repositories/releases/args4j/args4j/2.0.21/args4j-2.0.21.jar


# The class path consists of the lib directory and any _immediate_ subdirectories.


(2)
Install test dataset(s):

cd data
./testbed-nrw-prepare.sh


(3)
Build and run:

cd project
./run-testbed.sh

(Ant needs the current working directory set to project/ !)


Notes:
- "'on the fly' CRS transformation" needs to be enabled in QGIS's Project Properties, otherwise QGIS will ignore any CRS specified in the data.



